      "원시 데이터",
      "오버레이"
    ],
    "intent": "Faceted violin (density area per group) with raw data points overlaid as a centered jittered strip. KEY STRUCTURE: to facet a LAYERED chart you MUST use the 'facet' operator wrapping the layer spec ({facet, spec:{layer:[...]}}) — putting row/column in a layered spec's shared encoding silently fails to facet (all groups collapse into one cell). The density transform is scoped INSIDE the violin layer so the points are not aggregated. Points share the violin's density x-axis and are centered with x:{value:<half of width>} and jittered per-point via mark.xOffset {expr:'(random()-0.5)*N'}. Where __FIELD__ appears, substitute a real numeric column; 'group' is the grouping category",
    "spec": {
      "$schema": "https://vega.github.io/schema/vega-lite/v6.json",
      "data": {
        "values": []
      },
      "facet": {
        "column": {
